08/02/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- British Ambassador to Zagreb John Ramsden said Monday (7 February) that his country appreciates the readiness demonstrated by Croatian authorities to intensify efforts to arrest fugitive war crimes indictee Ante Gotovina. The retired general's extradition to the UN tribunal is a major condition for opening EU membership talks with Croatia in March.
In other news Monday, the State Electoral Commission sent a letter to Prime Minister Ivo Sanader and Parliamentary Speaker Vladimir Seks, proposing that legislation be adjusted to improve the election process. According to media reports, the commission is suggesting that six existing laws be united into a single electoral code to boost efficiency. (HINA, HRT - 07/02/05)
